{
  "text": "Many interesting information processing models are not serial-parallel networks. For example, models of dual tasks that postulate two or more bottlenecks very often employ a Wheatstone bridge and hence are not serial-parallel networks; see, e.g., [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , and [CITATION_3] . Cumulative distribution functions for the Wheatstone bridge are beyond the scope of this paper, but are discussed in [CITATION_4] . For convenience, we will call a network in which the process durations are mutually independent an independent network.",
  "citation_candidates": [
